What is ZTOCK

ZTOCK Mean Simple application design for implement publisher subscriber model.

How to That application work ?

Mainly that application contain 3 main parts

ZTOCK client

ZTOCK server

ZTOCK pub (like as publisher)

ZTOCK client User Guide:

1. How to install application on your computer:

You must want install JDK on your device. That application run on the JDK Platform binary.

You Must Want Copy Support Files (lib) To Your Default java Directory.

>>Example: Copy lib files to your JDK lib folder (fallow below path)

>>C: //Program Files//Java//jdk-15.0.1//lib

>>AbsoluteLayout.jar

>>Commons-lang3-3.8.1.jar >>commons-logging-1.2.jar >>hsqldb-2.5.0.jar >>jackcess-3.0.1.jar >>ucanaccess-5.0.1.jar

ZTOCK User Guide

Don’t remove any files come with the application. Make sure that files are in the same folder application located

>>Account.ZTOCK >>Bidding_Success.ZTOCK >>Can_Backup.ZTOCK >>Quick_guide.ZTOCK >>Requirements.ZTOCK >>Solutions.ZTOCK

.ZTOCK is .txt file format working with our client application. Don’t edit files because that files want to perform some actions in the application.

2.System Requirement

Windows Version: Windows 7 OR Above.

Other: Java JDK Must Be Run On the Device

JDK Version: SE Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_281-b09) OR Above

RAM: 50 MB > = 100MB

Storage: 10MB Minimum Storage Required

Connectivity: Wi-Fi Or Ethernet Connection Required But can be Run On Localhost

3.Get Started

Before you log in the system, you need to create local user account.

ZTOCK User Guide

After you fill requested fields press submit button for register. If you done correct system give you ZTOCK ID. Now press login button and Log into the system.

After you login system create a cache file for you. That file contain your details of you. There for two peoples can’t login to the system using same application in same time. Because that cache file store single value in the same time.

ZTOCK User Guide

Bidding Home Section

That is main and most important session in this application. That section allow to user make new biddings and subscribe, unsubscribe items.

When you access to this section. Application give you a unique temporary User ID

Ex : your user name + temp User name = USER ID

After access to this section you can connect to bidding server using valid IP address. And press Connect after connect you can subscribe Items and press Subscribe Button. You finished main steps now. After fallow this steps you can bid for items. If you add lower price than current price that bid is ignored. However server provide messages for you. Visit help section for more details.

Static view

When we click eye mark in bidding home we can see static view. In here we can see who won the bid and who lost, accepted bids and trashed bids.

In here we can see all the details of servers’ connection status. (Date, Time, Device IP address, Database Status, Port Address and Network Connection)

Zstock Publisher User Guide

Organization registration

Organization details

Organization registration

ZTOCK User Guide

In here we can register organizations using Register button. We have to enter company name, company code, price, security number, add profit. Also we can see server connection status in here. That register details store locally and server database.

Organization details

In here we can see organization bidding profits and details about company (organization name, organization code, price, profit, security code). Using Update Profit button we can update profits. Here also we can see server connection status.

Bidding updates

In here we can see server address, connection status, my stock id, current price. There is a special option called See live updates. Using See Live Updates button we can see live bidding updates in bidding time (5 minutes). Those updates will visible in terminal which in left side.
